# intake — dev secrets template (env-file)
#
# Setup:   cp .env.example .env   then fill in the values below.
# .env is gitignored — never commit your real keys.
#
# Load it before starting the relay. Examples:
#   bash/git-bash:  set -a; source .env; set +a; (cd relay && go run ./cmd/relay --config ../config.yaml)
#   docker:         docker run --env-file .env ...
#   compose:        env_file: .env
#   systemd:        EnvironmentFile=/etc/intake/.env
#
# SECRETS ONLY live here. Non-secret config (server addr, CORS, adapters, models,
# routing) is in config.yaml — see docs/specs/2026-05-27-configuration-and-secrets-design.md.
#
# Every secret also supports a *_FILE variant for Docker/k8s/Vault file mounts,
# e.g.  ANTHROPIC_API_KEY_FILE=/run/secrets/anthropic_key
# Do NOT set both a variable and its _FILE form (the relay errors on ambiguity).

# ── Active in Phase 1 — REQUIRED for the smoke ──────────────────────────────
# Anthropic API key from https://console.anthropic.com/ . Read server-side only;
# never sent to the browser.
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=

# ── Reserved for later phases — NOT wired yet, leave blank for now ───────────
# Phase 3 — adapters (free: chatwoot/fider; paid: zendesk/linear) + license:
# CHATWOOT_TOKEN=
# FIDER_API_KEY=
# ZENDESK_API_TOKEN=
# LINEAR_API_KEY=
# WEBHOOK_TOKEN=               # only if your webhook receiver requires an auth header
# INTAKE_LICENSE=              # base64 license JSON (paid adapters); or...
# INTAKE_LICENSE_FILE=         # path to license file 
#
# Phase 4 — email magic-link + host-app SSO:
# INTAKE_SMTP_PASS=
# INTAKE_EMAIL_JWT_SECRET=     # minimum 32 bytes
#
# Phase 5 — abuse protection:
# INTAKE_TURNSTILE_SECRET=     # Cloudflare Turnstile (or hCaptcha) secret
